Bunny has the source up on his page...it'd be a pain to mess with unless you rewrote a large part of it. It's not adding the GUI would be hard, it's be simple once you understood the existing program. But, he didn't use jump tables for routines and each routine basically HAS to be in the same spot for each update. Makes it 10x harder to work with it, so I have up the thought of attempting it, especially without a PP to begin with.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Sun Jun 24, 2012 5:19 pm</p><hr />
